Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with wigded caduceus symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Pencil '84'. Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 102, 46. Name Sosikles. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX BI 1151.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1021)
